'''Tajikarao Shrine''' (手力雄神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Nara (city)|Nara City]], [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]], at Hashimoto Town 39. It is an outer subordinate shrine of [[:en:Kasuga-taisha|Kasuga-taisha]]. The shrine is situated at the northern side of [[:en:Sanjō Street|Sanjō Street]]'s eastern edge, on a raised embankment. To the rear, separated by a Tsukiji wall, lies the Kōfuku-ji Kaikan.<ref name="shishi">Nara City History Editing Council, ''Nara City History: Shrines and Temples Edition'', {{ill|Yoshikawa Kōbunkan|ja|吉川学文館|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshikawa Kōbunkan|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, 1985, p.179</ref>

== History ==
According to legend, this location once featured a large willow tree, as recorded in the ''Nara Bowmei Satsukai'' (Records of Nara Districts):<ref name="annai">Information board on the shrine grounds</ref>
<blockquote>
There was a great willow tree within Tajikarao Shrine,
Whose branches and leaves flourished, covering the road.
Known as "Tajikarao Willow,"
In recent times, a strong wind damaged much of it,
Leaving only a remnant stump.
</blockquote>

In June 1895, during the widening of Sanjo Street, a depth of 1 ken and 6 sun was cut back, integrating it into the road.<ref name="shishi" /> In August of the same year, improvements were made, including the construction of a stone platform and minor relocation of the shrine building.<ref name="shishi" />

